snippet.textDisplay:
When I heard this song for the first time - I didn't quite like it. However it has grown on me . I think It's a fantastic song. sung , composed and rendered brilliantly.

My humble critique -  This song is governed by the tempo created by the two singers and the music.

What pulls the song backward and irks the flow/ tempo is Amit Trivedis voice.  He has tried to add another element which in my mind doesn't work well. If someone with a complementing voice ( replacing amits) been used , the song would be more impactful and would have enhanced it to the level it deserved. I say this with my utmost respect to Amit and his abilities .
